# Writing Markdown Docs

Write for a junior developer or a university research student. Keep it approachable.

## Links & citations

- Do NOT link to or cite other files unless it is truly necessary.
- Exception: DO link/reference when giving a guide to run code or showing command examples.

## Clarity

- Use plain, adequate wording. Explain jargon the first time it appears.
- Prefer short paragraphs and lists over dense text.

## Visuals

- Favor visual material to illustrate ideas: diagrams, images, and charts.
- Use fenced diagrams (e.g. Mermaid) or embedded images `![alt](path)` where they aid understanding.

Bad: `See control.c and estimator.c.` (unnecessary file links + a wall of dense text).

Good: a self-contained explanation paired with a visual, e.g. a Mermaid `flowchart`
showing Gyro + Accel feeding a fusion step that outputs the tilt angle.
